        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I personally like the idea of dropping `config.status.format` as a table and keeping only the function form. It will make API cleaner and more straightforward with a single source of truth for the signs.\r\nAnd for some advanced use cases when statusline signs need to differ from the sign column - it can be done in the format function.\r\n\r\nBut it's a breaking change and I don't have authority to greenlight it, so @justinmk it's your call.\r\n\r\nHowever if the breaking change is not an option, the PR looks good only need to update the doc for the `config.signs.text`, now it says:\r\n> A table mapping |diagnostic-severity| to the sign text to display in the sign column.\r\n\r\nAnd should become:\r\n> A table mapping |diagnostic-severity| to the sign text to display in the sign column and statusline (unless overriden in `vim.diagnostic.Opts.Status`.)",
